Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into ½-inch cubes.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water and pat dry with paper towels.

Place shrimp in a large #bowl{}. Add garlic, juice from half the lemon, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @italian seasoning{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat. Set aside to marinate, tossing occasionally.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, all the Fry Seasoning, and 2 tsp Italian Seasoning.

While shrimp marinates, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and @italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> Use all the scallion whites and Italian seasoning for 4 servings.

Stir in @israeli couscous{5%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @water{1 1/2%cups}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Use 3 cups water for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk together half the @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} until smooth. Slowly whisk in @olive oil{2%tbsp}; continue to whisk until combined and creamy. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use all the vinegar, all the mayonnaise, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings. Use 4 TBSP olive oil for 4.

Heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp with marinade; cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

== Salad ==

In a medium bowl, toss together @mixed greens{2%oz}, tomatoes, and mozzarella with as much dressing as you like. Season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}. Stir half the scallion greens, @butter{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice into pot with couscous. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous and salad between plates. Top couscous with shrimp, remaining scallion greens, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Garnish salad with @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.